<HEADLINE>
<P>
FORMER WYOMING GOV. ED HERSCHLER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ed Herschler, 71, a country lawyer who became Wyoming's only three-term 
governor, died of cancer in Cheyenne on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
He was 71. 
</P>
<P>
A Democrat in a predominantly Republican state, Herschler remained popular 
after leaving office in 1986 but declined to seek a fourth term. 
</P>
<P>
Herschler, who guided Wyoming through a boom in the energy industry, entered 
state politics in 1961 when he won a term in the House of Representatives after 
eight years as a county prosecutor. In 1970, Herschler lost his House seat, but 
returned to claim a surprising victory for governor four years later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
