<P>
MAN HOSPITALIZED AFTER DRIVE-BY SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 20-year-old man was shot Wednesday night near Chicano Park in the 2000 block 
of National Avenue in what police called the latest in a series of drive-by 
shootings. 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the San Diego Police Department said the unidentified man was 
shot about 7:25 p.m. The wounded man told police that the car was brown and was 
occupied by more than one person, police said. 
</P>
<P>
A supervisor at Physicians &amp; Surgeons Hospital said the man was checked in 
by a friend at 7:40 p.m. He was in stable condition Wednesday night with a 
gunshot wound to the buttocks. 
</P>
