<P>
WOMAN KILLED IN CRASH AS CAR FLIPS, HITS HOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman in her early 20s was killed Wednesday afternoon when the car she was 
driving veered out of control at high speed and flipped over, crashing into the 
back yard of a house in La Mesa, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The name of the victim was being withheld Wednesday night, pending notification 
of next of kin. She was the lone occupant of a 1980 Buick Regal that witnesses 
said became airborne and cleared a 6-foot chain-link fence after hurtling out 
of control on a curving section of Bancroft Drive, said Lt. Michael Wolfe of 
the La Mesa Police Department. 
</P>
