<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOCCER ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
TIE GIVES EDISON, OCEAN VIEW SHARE OF SECOND PLACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After 139 minutes of scoreless soccer, Ocean View High School broke through for 
a goal against Edison in a Sunset League boys' match Wednesday at Ocean View. 
</P>
<P>
Edison, the second-ranked team in the county, and No. 7 Ocean View had played 
100 minutes without a goal in their first league match. 
</P>
<P>
So when Peter Lak headed in a direct free kick by Greg Biggins in the final 
minute of the first half Wednesday, it seemed that that might be the winning 
goal. 
</P>
<P>
But Edison's Mike Hawks tied the score early in the second half on a pass from 
Brian Higgins and each team scored once in overtime. The final result was a 2-2 
tie that left the teams tied for second place with 5-1-3 records behind Marina 
(7-2 in league) with one match remaining, on Friday. Marina was a 2-0 winner 
over Fountain Valley Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Edison (13-5-5 overall) scored first in overtime when Higgins set up Hawks with 
another assist. Ocean View (13-4-5 overall) tied it with near the end of the 
first 10-minute period, when Scott Bauer threw a pass from the sideline that 
Andrew Wind headed into the goal. 
</P>
<P>
"Was that a great game or what?" said Ocean View Coach Paul Kollar. "Back and 
forth, up and down the field. That was an outstanding game." MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</TEXT>
