COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ST. MARY'S STOPS UC IRVINE IN BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gil Orta went two for three with two runs scored and two runs batted in to lead 
St. Mary's to a 7-4 victory over host UC Irvine in a nonconference baseball 
game Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Orta had a two-run single to key St. Mary's three-run second inning and Randy 
Cooper and Mike Zanski had run-scoring singles in the seventh inning to lead 
St. Mary's (1-2). 
</P>
<P>
Cooper went three for five with two RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
Osmar DeChavez went two for four with one run scored and Brian Young homered in 
the fifth for host UC Irvine (2-3). 
</P>
<P>
Tom Shildemeyer was the winning pitcher and Bill Christ had the save. David 
Bladow (1-1) took the loss. 
</P>
