<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ROYAL CLINCHES SHARE OF LEAGUE TITLE, 55-52 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF RILEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Royal High used clutch baskets from Chad Smith and Jared Byrne to cap a wild 
fourth quarter that featured five lead changes and hand host Westlake a 55-52 
loss in a battle for the Marmonte League title Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The win gave Royal (20-5, 9-2), which trailed by 11 points early in the third 
quarter, at least a share of its first league title since 1971. 
</P>
<P>
Westlake (13-9, 7-4), in the hunt for its first league title, fell to third 
place behind Simi Valley (16-8, 8-3). 
</P>
<P>
Simi Valley, which defeated Thousand Oaks, 63-56, will travel to Royal on 
Friday in the final game of the regular season. Simi Valley must win to forge a 
tie and give the Pioneers a share of their fifth consecutive title. 
</P>
<P>
Smith, a 6-foot-5 senior who was hampered by foul trouble, hit a 15-foot jump 
shot to give Royal a 53-52 lead with two minutes left. After Westlake's B. J. 
Sena (15 points) blocked a shot and gave the Warriors possession with 19 
seconds left, Byrne immediately stole the ball underneath Westlake's basket and 
scored to give Royal a 55-52 lead with 17 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Westlake called a timeout with 15 seconds left to set up a game-tying basket, 
but Dave Monheim's three-point attempt twice bounced from the rim with four 
seconds left. JEFF RILEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA020890-0046 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 173182 </DOCID>
