<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COLLEGE BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TODAY'S HIGHLIGHTS 
</P>
<P>
WEST COAST CONFERENCE 
</P>
<P>
UNIVERSITY OF SAN DIEGO (10-10, 5-3) at GONZAGA (6-15, 1-8), 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
TV -- None. Radio -- None. 
</P>
<P>
USD, winner of three in a row and seven of 10, is tied with Pepperdine for 
second in the WCC heading into two critical games in the Pacific Northwest. The 
Toreros defeated both opponents in San Diego last week: Gonzaga, 68-58, on 
Saturday and Portland, 76-55, on Thursday. John Jerome leads the Toreros in 
scoring (19.3) and rebounding (7.0). In WCC games, he is averaging 20 points, 
Pat Holbert 14 and Craig Cottrell 10.1. Holbert is second in the nation in 
three-point percentage at .559, behind Arkansas' Lee Mayberry (.563), and has 
made 27 of 31 free throws. Guard Gylan Dottin (broken nose) will be able to 
play for the first time in three games. Center Brooks Barnhard (ankle) is 
questionable. Gonzaga, loser of six in a row, is led by senior guard Jim McPhee 
(23.2 average), who had 26 against USD Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
