<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: SIGNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Punter Jason Savorn of Cordova High School (Rancho Cordova) and wide receiver 
Jeff Speech of Riordan High School (San Francisco) have orally committed to San 
Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
Savorn, 6-feet-2, 195 pounds, is a top prospect to replace Joe Santos, who 
completed his eligibility after punting for SDSU for the past two seasons. 
Savorn has enrolled at SDSU for the second semester and will participate in 
spring drills. He averaged 47 yards per punt last season and also kicked for 
Cordova. 
</P>
<P>
Speech is 6-1, 170, and described by Riordan Coach Liam Watters as having "good 
speed, fairly good height and very good hands." SCOTT MILLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
