</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ashton-Tate Corp.: The Torrance firm reported a fourth-quarter net loss of $1 
million, contrasted with net income of $13.4 million a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue fell 29% to $62.1 million. The maker of microcomputer software products 
attributed the results for the quarter and for fiscal 1989 to reduced revenues, 
and said a gain on the sale of its interest in Sybase Inc. was offset by 
writeoffs. For the year ended Dec. 31, the maker of microcomputer software 
products lost $28.6 million, contrasted with net income of $47.7 million in 
fiscal 1988, which ended Jan. 31, 1989. Revenue for the year fell 14% to $265.3 
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
