<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hammer Teams with HBO on Miniseries: Russian history in the 20th Century will 
be the subject of a 10-part fictional HBO miniseries set to be co-produced by 
industrialist Armand Hammer, whose interest in and influence in the Soviet 
Union has spanned several decades. 
</P>
<P>
The project, tentatively titled "Mother Russia" and set to air in 1992, will be 
based on fact. Historical events will provide the backdrop for its focus on 
individual fictional lives. It will be filmed entirely on location in the 
Soviet Union, with pre-production scheduled for this fall and shooting to start 
in February, 1991. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
