<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: DISTRICT 3 HONORS CAL LUTHERAN'S LEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brenda Lee, a senior guard for Cal Lutheran, was named NAIA District 3 Player 
of the Week after scoring 45 points and grabbing 37 rebounds in two games. 
</P>
<P>
Lee had a career-high 18 rebounds and scored 27 points in an 80-79 victory over 
Southern California College on Jan. 30. She followed that performance with 19 
rebounds and 18 points Saturday in an 82-69 loss to Point Loma Nazarene. 
</P>
<P>
Lee, who is averaging 14.7 points and 11.7 rebounds, is Cal Lutheran's only 
basketball player, man or woman, to be named district player of the week this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
Tisha Walker of Thousand Oaks was 15th among a field of 16 after the compulsory 
figures Wednesday in the U. S. Figure Skating Championships in Salt Lake City. 
</P>
<P>
Walker, 15, competing in the senior ladies division, will move on to the 
original program tonight. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Briggs, an All-American linebacker at Moorpark College, has committed to 
West Virginia after considering Utah, San Jose State and Penn State, Moorpark 
Coach Jim Bittner said. 
</P>
<P>
Several other members of Moorpark's 9-2 Orange County Bowl team also have 
chosen schools, according to Bittner. 
</P>
<P>
Linebacker Ray Mosones is already taking classes at Sonoma State and receiver 
Rick Wright is attending Cal Poly San Luis Obispo. Linebacker David Joller also 
will attend San Luis Obispo. 
</P>
<P>
Defensive back Jim Hand has gone to Culver-Stockton College in Canton, Mo., and 
defensive back Troy Thomas is looking at Cal State Northridge and Redlands, 
Bittner said. 
</P>
<P>
Bittner said running back John Brown will sign with Southern Utah State on 
Friday and that center Carlos Hernandez is leaning toward Southern Oregon. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Lieberthal of Westlake High has made an oral commitment to attend Arizona 
State. 
</P>
<P>
Lieberthal, a catcher, batted .408 last season and he had four home runs, three 
doubles and nine stolen bases. 
</P>
<P>
Beth Welch, a three-year starter as setter on the Washington State women's 
volleyball team, has transferred to Cal State Northridge and will be eligible 
as a senior next season, Coach Walt Ker said. Welch is a former Thousand Oaks 
High standout. 
</P>
<P>
With the addition of Welch, Ker plans to sign only two high school recruits -- 
a middle blocker and a left-side hitter. 
</P>
<P>
Roger Evans, the Simi Valley High girls' track coach, will coach the Sport For 
Understanding track team that is traveling to Europe this summer. 
</P>
<P>
Participants and volunteer coaches will live with host families. 
</P>
<P>
A fund-raiser, an all-you-can-eat pancake breakfast to benefit the Channel 
Islands High football stadium fund, will be held Saturday from 7 to 11 a.m. in 
the school cafeteria. 
</P>
<P>
Information: 805-385-2746. 
</P>
</TEXT>
