<P>
SUIT AGAINST CITY REINSTATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reversing an earlier decision, a Pomona Superior Court judge ruled that a 
countersuit filed against the city by a former redevelopment consultant will be 
heard in court. 
</P>
<P>
Monday's decision by Superior Court Judge Thomas Nuss will allow Fred Lyte, who 
was fired by the City Council in December, 1988, to countersue the city for 
$1.38 million that Lyte says he is owed. 
</P>
<P>
Early last year, the city sued Lyte, charging he recommended projects from 
which he stood to benefit financially. The city's suit claims Lyte owes 
Irwindale more than $1 million in commissions he received on redevelopment 
projects. 
