<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wesson Refinery to Close: Beatrice-Hunt-Wesson will close its Wesson oil 
refinery in Fullerton, eliminating about 100 jobs, a company spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
No date was set. The company told workers that the refinery would be closed for 
"economic and strategic reasons," the spokeswoman said. The 1,500 employees at 
Beatrice-Hunt-Wesson's Fullerton headquarters and another 900 employees -- 
including seasonal employees -- at the tomato-processing and can-making plants 
also in Fullerton are not affected. 
</P>
