<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRITAIN HELPS ROMANIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Britain said Wednesday that it is sending a million disposable syringes to 
Romania to help prevent the spread of AIDS. Romanian doctors have appealed for 
Western help to contain an AIDS epidemic among children in hospitals and 
orphanages. Hundreds of the children have been infected by blood transfusions 
or contaminated needles. 
</P>
