<P>
PATTI DAVIS' MARRIAGE ON ROCKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Patti Davis, Ronald and Nancy Reagan's estranged daughter, is now estranged 
from her husband, it was reported today. 
</P>
<P>
Davis, 37, has been living apart from yoga instructor Paul Grilley, whom she 
married Aug. 14, 1984, for about a month, the New York Daily News said. "They 
are divorcing," a friend of Davis told the newspaper. Davis' acting career 
failed to take off, and she turned to writing novels -- first with "Home 
Front," an unflattering parallel of her family, and then "Deadfall," a thriller 
about Nicaraguan policy. Neither pleased her parents, according to reports. 
</P>
