<TEXT>
<P>
No one picked all six winning numbers in the California Lottery's Wednesday 
night "Lotto 6-49" game, leaving a $4.8-million jackpot untouched, Lottery 
officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
The $4.8-million jackpot will roll over to help build the Saturday night 
jackpot to an estimated $10 million, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
There was one ticket with five numbers plus the bonus number worth $1.3 
million. Another 173 tickets with five of six will share a $679,000 prize pool, 
each receiving $3,929. 
