NATION; 
</P>
<P>
IRAN TERROR THREAT WORRIES U.S. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United States is deeply concerned about the possibility of a terrorist 
attack against Americans or U.S. installations in Europe to coincide with the 
11th anniversary of the Islamic revolution in Iran, the State Department said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy spokesman Richard Boucher recalled that a threat advisory was issued 
last December and he said that threat continues. 
</P>
<P>
The anniversary of Iran's revolution is this Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Boucher added that the United States has no specific information about the 
alleged terrorist operation or its target. 
</P>
<P>
"If further credible or specific information on this threat develops, the 
department will issue additional alerts to travelers and other concerned 
parties," he said. 
</P>
<P>
He added that the department is encouraging travelers to Europe to exercise 
caution but that Americans are not being urged to cancel plans they may have to 
visit the Continent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
