<P>
ISRAELI RIOT DEVICE THROWS GRAVEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In its latest effort to halt rioting in the occupied territories, the Israeli 
army has introduced a jeep-mounted gravel thrower that spews out 600 egg-sized 
rocks a minute, Israel radio said today. 
</P>
<P>
The battery-powered device weighs 66 pounds, can be mounted on a jeep and 
operated by one soldier. It can throw the egg-sized stones 75 yards, the report 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The new device is the latest addition to the army's growing anti-uprising 
arsenal that also includes tear gas and various types of rubber, plastic and 
metal bullets. 
</P>
<P>
Israel has drawn international criticism for firing guns at stone-throwers, 
most of them children and teen-agers. But army officials contend that troops 
use live ammunition only when their lives are in danger. 
</P>
</TEXT>
