<P>
SHANDLING TO EMCEE GRAMMYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Comedian Garry Shandling will be host of the 32nd annual Grammy Awards 
presentation this month, the Academy of Recording Arts &amp; Sciences announced 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Shandling is best known as the slow-talking star of the comedy television 
series "It's Garry Shandling's Show." 
</P>
<P>
The Grammys will be presented Feb. 21 during a live, three-hour CBS-TV 
broadcast from the Shrine Auditorium. 
</P>
<P>
The awards honor artistic and technical recording achievements in 77 
categories. 
</P>
<P>
Shandling was a writer for television comedies before developing a stand-up 
routine of his own in the mid-1970s. He has also appeared on "The Tonight Show 
Starring Johnny Carson" -- for which he often served as a guest host -- and 
"Late Night With David Letterman." 
</P>
</TEXT>
