<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
DOKES TO FIGHT RUDDOCK IN APRIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael Dokes and Razor Ruddock couldn't get fights with heavyweight champion 
Mike Tyson, so they'll fight each other. 
</P>
<P>
Their April 4 meeting at Madison Square Garden was announced today in New York, 
and it's being billed as "Fighting Mad" -- not at each other but at promoter 
Don King for sidestepping them in the heavyweight championship chase. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't know if Tyson's trying to avoid me, or whether King is manipulating 
him," Dokes said at a midtown Manhattan luncheon. "But I would like to ask him 
personally." 
</P>
<P>
Last August, King reportedly turned down Dokes' asking price of $3 million to 
fight Tyson and offered $1 million, which Dokes considers chump change. 
</P>
<P>
Instead, King made a deal to co-promote a fight with Murad Muhammad between 
Tyson and Ruddock. Tyson pulled out of that November bout with a minor illness, 
then signed to fight Buster Douglas, whom he meets Sunday in Tokyo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
